-- RIM's co-CEO to buy Nashville Predators: WSJ
-- 
-- Thu May 24, 2007 3:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/24/us-rim-ceo-hockey-idUSN2429832920070524

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Jim Balsillie, co-chief executive of BlackBerry maker Research In Motion Ltd. RIM.TO, has agreed to buy the National Hockey League's Nashville Predators, the Wall Street Journal reported on its Web site on Thursday. 

 Balsillie will pay about $200 million for the Predators, the Journal said, citing unnamed sources. RIM could not be reached immediately.